<H3> <TI>   Zhu Rongji Meets Japanese Economic Figures, Officials </TI></H3>
<H4>   Visits Emperor Akihito </H4>
<F P=102> OW2602084094 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1122 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2602084094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<FÊP=106> [By reporter <PERSON>Zhang Huanli</PERSON> (1728 3562 0448)] </F>
  [Text] <LOCATION>Tokyo</LOCATION>, 25 Feb (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice Premier <PERSON>Zhu 
Rongji</PERSON>, who is making a formal friendly visit to <LOCATION>Japan</LOCATION>, paid a 
courtesy call on Japanese Emperor Akihito at the palace here 
<TIME>this morning</TIME>. 
  Expressing a warm welcome to <PERSON>Zhu Rongji</PERSON>, <PERSON>Emperor Akihito</PERSON> 
said: "I was glad to hear that Vice Premier <PERSON>Zhu</PERSON> has met a number 
of people from both <ORGANIZATION>Japanese Government</ORGANIZATION> and nongovernment 
organizations during the past two days and achieved progress in 
promoting bilateral friendship." 
  Zhu Rongji conveyed to Emperor Akihito sincere greetings and 
good wishes from President <PERSON>Jiang Zemin</PERSON> and Premier <PERSON>Li Peng</PERSON>. 
Emperor <PERSON>Akihito</PERSON> expressed his thanks and asked <PERSON>Zhu Rongji</PERSON> to 
convey his greetings to President <PERSON>Jiang Zemin</PERSON> and other Chinese 
leaders. 
  Emperor <PERSON>Akihito</PERSON> pleasantly recalled his visit to <LOCATION>China</LOCATION> in 
<DATE>1992</DATE>. He said: "During my trip to <LOCATION>China</LOCATION>, I went to <LOCATION>Xian</LOCATION> and 
<LOCATION>Shanghai</LOCATION>. When I was in <LOCATION>Shanghai</LOCATION>, I was impressed by <LOCATION>China</LOCATION>'s 
rapid economic growth." 
  Zhu Rongji briefed <PERSON>Emperor Akihito</PERSON> on Sino-Japanese 
relations, and particularly the rapid development in <LOCATION>China</LOCATION>'s 
economic cooperation and trade with <LOCATION>Japan</LOCATION>. 
  Emperor <PERSON>Akihito</PERSON> was pleased with the rapid development of 
Sino-Japanese relations. 
  Present at the meeting was Chinese Ambassador to <LOCATION>Japan</LOCATION> Xu 
Dungxin. 

</TEXT>

