three <LOCATION>Tokyo</LOCATION> train stations that stopped traffic on two major
commuter lines, police reported.
   Fires erupted at four Shinto shrines in <LOCATION>Tokyo</LOCATION>, including one
less than a mile from <PERSON>Akihito</PERSON>'s residence, destroying two.
   Japanese flags lined the main streets in the <LOCATION>Ginza</LOCATION> shopping
district, where cars and trucks painted with rightist slogans
paraded. Speakers blared ``Long live the emperor,'' as riot police
stood by.
